Description: Fragment of neck and rising handle to sharpish turn of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp. Clay fine buff-brown.
Curator's comments: Name Philainios. Perhaps the same as Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 88, 4. Pencilled '3' plus a second sign.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0768)
Acquisition name: Donated by: Sir Charles Thomas Newton (perhaps)
